<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dislike2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dislike,</orth> vb. 1) to disapprove, to regard with ill-will or disgust; a) tr.: <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.73" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.227" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 227</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 113</bibl>.<lb />b) absol.: <cit><quote>with a heavy, dark, --ing eye,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 182" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 182</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>not minding whether I d. or no,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 2.5.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 5, 20</bibl></cit>. Followed by <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>thou --st of virtue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.130" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 130</bibl></cit>.
<lb />2) to displease: <cit><quote>if either thee d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 2, 61</bibl></cit> (Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>displease</emph>). <cit><quote>it --s me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 49</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>